  <body class="min-h-screen flex flex-col items-center justify-start pt-16 pb-16 px-4 relative overflow-hidden">
    <div class="scanlines"></div>

    <h1 class="game-hero text-4xl font-black mb-2 text-center">THE LAUGHING FUNERAL</h1>
    <p class="text-[#0ff1ce] text-center mb-8">About this game</p>

    <div style="max-width: 700px; width: 100%;">

      <div class="content-block">
        <p class="section-title">Setting — Nocturne Aeturnus</p>
        <p style="color: #a0a0b0; line-height: 1.7;">
          A gothic frequency of perpetual twilight — deep indigo sky, violet Sorrowful Moon, air thick with petrichor and the mineral tang of crystallized feelings. The architecture is gothic: tall spires, flying buttresses, facades that pulse with emotional resonance visible in the stonework. Grief crystallizes into spires. Joy is rarer, more volatile, more dangerous.
        </p>
        <p style="color: #a0a0b0; line-height: 1.7; margin-top: 0.75rem;">
          The funeral house is three hundred years old, built during the Third Sorrow Renaissance, its walls encrusted with crystallized tears. Nothing has ever gone wrong here. Until now.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="content-block">
        <p class="section-title">The Mystery</p>
        <p style="color: #a0a0b0; line-height: 1.7;">
          Thaddeus Mourning died. A funeral was held. At that funeral — in a place where laughter during mourning is a structural violation of the social fabric — everyone present laughed. Clearly. Joyfully. Without exception.
        </p>
        <p style="color: #a0a0b0; line-height: 1.7; margin-top: 0.75rem;">
          The Ministry classified it. The dead person's sister couldn't. She remembered Klaus — the last investigator who refused to look away. She contacted him through a frequency she thought was secure.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="content-block">
        <p class="section-title">Baron Klaus</p>
        <p style="color: #a0a0b0; line-height: 1.7;">
          Investigator. Procurement specialist. A man who left Nocturne fifteen years ago under circumstances he has never explained. He is not a detective. He is a man who does not look away. In Nocturne, that is considered the same thing.
        </p>
        <p style="color: #a0a0b0; line-height: 1.7; margin-top: 0.75rem;">
          Klaus goes back. The Ministry made his position obsolete last time. This time, he has the Ephergent.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="content-block">
        <p class="section-title">Barry's Field Note</p>
        <p style="color: #a0a0b0; line-height: 1.7;">
          In the funeral house archive room, Klaus finds a field note. The handwriting is Prime Material. It's Barry Kowalski's.
        </p>
        <p style="color: #a0a0b0; line-height: 1.7; margin-top: 0.5rem; font-style: italic;">
          "I came here looking for a signal. I found a silence. The silence was louder. If you're reading this, you've found the same silence. Here's what I found: the signal was never here. The signal was waiting for someone to stop listening so it could be heard. Don't stop listening. The silence is the message."
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="content-block">
        <p class="section-title">Game Info</p>
        <ul style="color: #a0a0b0; line-height: 1.9; padding-left: 1.5rem;">
          <li>Engine: Godot 4 (HTML5 export)</li>
          <li>Size: 13.8 MB</li>
          <li>Price: Free forever</li>
          <li>Play time: 45–90 minutes</li>
          <li>Completionists: 2–3 hours</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

    </div>

    <div class="flex flex-row justify-center gap-4 mt-8">
      <a href="/games/the-laughing-funeral/play/" class="nav-link font-bold">Play Now</a>
      <a href="/games/" class="nav-link">All Games</a>
    </div>

  </body>
